Reasoning: The paper deals with algorithmic problems in the setting where input data is partitioned on multiple servers, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC). The problems addressed in the paper involve computing functions of large data sets, which could be classified under machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also mentions computing frequency moments and separable functions, which are related to information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper deals with computing correlations in data sets, which could be classified under data structures (cs.DS).
